  "datePublished": "2025-12-26",
  "description": "The natural numbers ℕ = {0, 1, 2, 3, ...} are the numbers generated from [zero](./zero.md) by repeated application of the [successor](./successor.md) operation. They are characterized by the [Peano axioms](./peano-axioms.md): zero is a natural number, every natural number has a successor, zero is not a successor, the successor function is injective, and [induction](./induction.md) holds.",
